Student Attendance

These tables list the students in each grade who are among the bottom 10% in terms of Average Daily Attendance (ADA). ADA is calcualte separately for each student and simply gives the percentage of time a student has attended school since they enrolled at the school. Consequenlty, a recently enrolled student missing only 5 days would appear on this list if theyve only been enrolled 15 days. Such a student would have a calculated ADA of 66.6%, meaning theyve attended school two thirds of the time since they enrolled and have missed 1/3 of the days since enrolling.

The set of students in the 10th percentile of lower is calculated separately for each grade level at each school.

Suspensions

In this report the metric suspensions represents days absent due to suspensions and not the number of suspension events. That is, a student recieving a 3-day suspension would appear in this report as having 3 suspensions (i.e., three absenses due to being out of school serving a suspension).
